PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778854269
OL,3,CWhat are the symptoms of meningitis
OL,4,Cand what is the advice?
OL,6,FSepticaemia can also cause a
OL,7,Fcharacteristic rash that does not fade
OL,8,Fwhen pressed against a glass.
OL,10,FHow is meningitis treated?
OL,12,FHospital treatment is recommended by
OL,13,Fthe NHS for all cases of bacterial
OL,14,Fmeningitis.
OL,16,FTreatments include antibiotics and
OL,17,Ffluids administered directly into a
OL,18,Fvein, oxygen if there are breathing
OL,19,Fdifficulties, and in some cases
OL,20,Fsteroid medication to prevent swelling
OL,21,Faround the brain.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
